description:
&lt;p&gt;Nuffield Health is Britain’s largest not-for-profit healthcare organisation. Join us as a Bank Pharmacy Technician in our York Hospital and play your part in building a healthier nation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Work with a close knit team who support one another to deliver excellent pharmaceutical care to our patients. As our bank technician you will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provide support to the pharmacist and department, covering annual leave, absence and busy periods&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Person&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;To succeed as a bank technician, you will need:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NVQ Level 3 Pharmacy service qualification or equivalent is required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Proven experience in a pharmacy setting&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be registered as a Pharmacy Technician with the General Pharmaceutical Society.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to use  your initiative.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Holiday in line with the Working Time Directive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Access to our Pension Scheme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Discounted gym membership at £15.00 a month that they need to set up directly with the club. Discount does not extend to partners and family members.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary - £12.82 per hour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date - 15/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location - York&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contract Type - Bank&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working on the bank means you are not contracted to a set number of hours per week, but instead work on an ad-hoc basis to suit the needs of the business and your availability.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Applications will be considered as they are received and interviews will be arranged accordingly. We reserve the right to close adverts early, for example, where we have received an unprecedented high volume of applications. Therefore please apply early to ensure you are considered for the post. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
